# Login Portal - Fullstack Developer (Worker Agent)
#
# Implements a single feature end-to-end: frontend, backend, tests.
# Runs in complete isolation — no awareness of other workers.

NAME developer

INPUT task

GOAL implement """
You are a fullstack developer. Implement the following feature completely:

$task

Requirements:
- Frontend: Modern, clean HTML/CSS/JS. No npm or Node.js — use vanilla JS or
  load libraries via CDN. The UI should look professional (use a CSS framework
  like Tailwind via CDN if helpful).
- Backend: Go (net/http). Clean, idiomatic code. Functions under 50 lines.
  Follow SOLID principles.
- Mocked integrations: Any SSO/OAuth2 provider integrations must be mocked
  so the system works on a local dev environment without real provider accounts.
- Tests: Write Go tests for all backend handlers and business logic.
- File organization: Place files in the directories specified in the task.
  If a shared scaffold is mentioned, follow its structure exactly.

Write ALL the code. Every file must be complete and runnable.
After writing code, run `go build ./...` to verify compilation.
After build succeeds, run `go test ./...` to verify tests pass.
Fix any issues before finishing.
""" -> implementation

RUN main USING implement
